'''Arthur Petrie''' (died 19 April 1787)<ref>Dowden, J., ''The bishops of Scotland'', 1912</ref> was the 37th [[bishop]] of the [[Diocese of Moray, Ross and Caithness|Diocese of Ross and Moray]] of the [[Scottish Episcopal Church]]. He was one of the three bishops to consecrate [[Samuel Seabury (1729–1796)|Samuel Seabury]], an American [[Episcopal Church in the United States of America|Episcopal]] priest as a bishop in 1784.

The Glasgow Mercury newspaper<ref>Glasgow Mercury, Wednesday 25 April to Wednesday 2 May 1787.</ref> reporting his death at Micklefollo, described him as 'a dignified clergyman of the Episcopal Church in Scotland, much respected'.

