'''Parmatma Ek Sevak''', ({{lang-mr|परमात्मा एक सेवक}}), is a minor sect of [[Hinduism]] mostly restricted to eastern Vidarbha and central India.  The sect was founded by [[Baba Jumdev]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india/vice-prez-releases-postal-stamp-of-jumdev-baba-28607.html |title=Vice Prez releases postal stamp of Jumdev Baba |publisher=India TV |date=2013-10-01 |accessdate=2017-12-31}}</ref>

The sect commands worship of one god and abstinence from alcohol.  Though being a part of Hinduism, the sect forbids its followers to worship any of the Hindu deities.{{Citation needed|date=December 2017}}

